track_notes: This route is well-maintained trail the whole way and has sections that are quite flat. I chose to do an out-and-back to Union Hills first then turn up to Union Hills North. However a shorter hike would be to take the V Trail shortcut across - that trail would likely have been a better choice but I was unsure at the time. Park at Phoenix Sonoran Preserve. Note that this is a popular urban trail system with hikers, bikers, and horses and it is busy, even on weekdays, you probably will be aharing the summit with others.
track_title: Union Hills and Unionn Hills North Double Activation

track_notes: This is the trail used by the locals to access Union Hills. Head north on 2nd street until you notice led lights lining the road. There is parking on the west side of the road just before the LED lights. Park there and walk north on the paved road and enter the mountain preserve. There is a sign when entering the preserve. This is a much shorter route. If you do both peaks as shown by KR7RK there is a shorter route that does not take you almost back to the trailhead. It appears on the SOTA map.
track_title: Shortcut to Union Hills MN-125 from 2nd street neighborhood

track_notes:
The fast route up the South side of the hill is closed, as of 12/31/21. These side routes are pretty much the same distance around without any notable difference between the two. 

Park on the dirt shoulder, west side of 2nd Street about 1/8th mile short of the trail sign. Easy walk. No issues.

There are two ways to take the Great Horned Owl trail around the summit to the north side where the trail goes up to the summit, but the east side has a couple hundred feet less of elevation gain and loss and is marginally shorter than the west side. On my last activation I took the use trail down from the summit but that is now marked explicitly closed for habitat restoration (photo on sotl.as) so this route around the east is the fastest way to the top.
track_title: Shortest current route to the summit

track_notes: This is the route between Union Hills and Dixie Mountain
